* Dave Booth (2003–2004), (2009–2010)
* Syed Nayeemuddin (2004–2005)
* Derrick Pereira (2005–2009)

==Other department==
===Field hockey===
The club had its field hockey team that participated in both the Beighton Cup and Bombay Gold Cup. Two of the club&#x27;s notable players are Sameer Dad – who represented India at the 1998 Asian Games and 1998 Men&#x27;s Hockey World Cup, and Baljit Singh Dhillon – who appeared at the Summer Olympics.

;Honours
*Bombay Gold Cup
**Runners-up (4): 1974, 1976, 1982, 1986
*Guru Tegh Bahadur Gold Cup
**Champions (1): 1980

