<text>The mayor of Regina is head of Regina City Council, the governing body of Regina, the capital city of the Canadian province of Saskatchewan. The 36th and current mayor of the city of Regina is Chad Bachynski, who was first elected in the 2024 municipal election. The following is a list of mayors of Regina, including those who served as mayor of the town of Regina between 1884 and 1903.

From 1920 to 1926, Regina mayors were elected using instant-runoff voting. All other times a first past the post system was used.

